WEBVTT

00:05.538 --> 00:06.506 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:06.539 --> 00:07.474 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.507 --> 00:09.209 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:09.242 --> 00:11.011 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY, White House
Budget Director:
We're trying to drive the
economic benefit

00:11.044 --> 00:14.581 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
here to the taxpayers in the
middle.

00:14.614 --> 00:19.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: White House
Budget Director
Mick Mulvaney joins me to
explain the administration's

00:19.919 --> 00:25.959 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
tax reform proposal and
President Trump's
plan to get a spending bill
passed.

00:25.992 --> 00:31.698 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Also ahead, a look at the first
100 days of
the Trump presidency, the
progress and setbacks

00:31.731 --> 00:34.534 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the domestic front for the
new administration.

00:34.567 --> 00:42.575 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Then: a wall keeping people and
wildlife out
-- how a political divide could
endanger animals

00:42.609 --> 00:44.377 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
living along the U.S.-Mexico
border.

00:44.411 --> 00:47.347 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SERGIO AVILA-VILLEGAS,
Arizona-Sonora Desert
Museum: Long-term, this could be
a division

00:47.380 --> 00:52.485 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of genetical populations, where
a group of
animals from one side cannot
reproduce with

00:52.519 --> 00:56.790 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
another group of animals,
breaking the connectivity,
creating some genetical
problems.

00:56.823 --> 01:00.360 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:00.393 --> 01:04.431 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:04.464 --> 01:16.009 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The Trump
administration is
out with the broad strokes of
what it says

01:16.042 --> 01:19.746 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
would be the largest tax reform
in U.S. history.

01:19.779 --> 01:25.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The plan's main features,
released today,
include cutting corporate tax
rates to 15

01:25.485 --> 01:27.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
percent from 35 percent.

01:27.487 --> 01:33.193 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It would also consolidate
existing income
tax brackets into just three,
ranging from

01:33.226 --> 01:35.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
10 percent to 35 percent.

01:35.161 --> 01:39.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it would double the standard
deduction,
while repealing the estate tax.

01:39.899 --> 01:44.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
At a White House briefing,
Treasury Secretary
Steven Mnuchin promised the plan
will not

01:44.871 --> 01:46.706 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
make the deficit worse.

01:46.739 --> 01:50.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STEVEN MNUCHIN, U.S. Treasury
Secretary: This
will pay for itself with growth
and with reduced

01:50.944 --> 01:56.349 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
reduction of different
deductions, and closing
loopholes.

01:56.382 --> 02:01.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will be working very closely,
as I said,
with the House and Senate to
turn this into

02:01.421 --> 02:07.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a bill that can be passed and
the president
can sign, and there's lots and
lots of details

02:07.627 --> 02:09.696 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going into how that will pay for
itself.

02:09.729 --> 02:14.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Republican
leaders said the
plan offers critical guideposts
for a tax

02:14.300 --> 02:19.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
overhaul, but Democrats called
it a massive
tax break for the wealthy.

02:19.906 --> 02:25.478 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On another issue, Secretary
Mnuchin said today
that President Trump -- quote --
"has no intention"

02:25.512 --> 02:29.048 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of making his own tax returns
public.

02:29.082 --> 02:33.753 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Congress moved closer today to
trying to prevent
a government shutdown on
Saturday.

02:33.786 --> 02:38.625 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats said one stumbling
block apparently
fell away when the White House
agreed to continue

02:38.658 --> 02:42.862 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
subsidies for millions of poor
people under
Obamacare.

02:42.896 --> 02:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, conservative House
Republicans
announced that they will back a
newly revised

02:47.734 --> 02:51.271 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
plan to repeal and replace
Obamacare.

02:51.304 --> 02:55.108 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It is not yet clear if moderates
will go along.

02:55.141 --> 02:59.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is word that President
Trump has settled
on a course of action against
North Korea.

02:59.846 --> 03:06.452 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A top national security official
says it begins
with diplomacy, but includes a
range of options.

03:06.486 --> 03:13.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That word came as all 100
senators took a
bus caravan to the White House
for a classified

03:13.159 --> 03:14.594 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
briefing.

03:14.627 --> 03:17.530 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Democrat Chris Coons of Delaware
was among
those who spoke afterwards.

03:17.564 --> 03:19.299 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

03:19.332 --> 03:21.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHRIS COONS (D), Delaware: I was
encouraged
that they chose to brief the
entire Senate.

03:22.001 --> 03:27.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think the -- it was a
sobering briefing,
in which it was clear just how
much thought

03:27.040 --> 03:32.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and planning is going into
preparing military
options, if called for, and a
diplomatic strategy

03:32.979 --> 03:40.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that strikes me as clear-eyed
and well -- well-proportioned
to the threat.

03:40.153 --> 03:43.990 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: House members had
their briefing
later at the Capitol.

03:44.023 --> 03:49.329 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And North Korea issued a new
warning that
it will -- quote -- "go to the
end," apparently

03:49.362 --> 03:54.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
meaning a nuclear strike, if
there is an all-out
war with the U.S.

03:54.400 --> 04:00.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
China today unveiled its first
domestically
built aircraft carrier, the
latest step in

04:00.039 --> 04:02.275 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a major naval expansion.

04:02.308 --> 04:06.946 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The vessel slowly slipped into
the water in
the port city of Dalian to much
fanfare.

04:06.980 --> 04:13.586 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It is expected to become
operational by 2020,
after undergoing sea trials.

04:13.620 --> 04:17.991 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump today decried a
new legal
blow to his immigration policy.

04:18.024 --> 04:23.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Tuesday, a federal district
judge in San
Francisco blocked his order to
withhold funding

04:23.963 --> 04:30.003 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from so-called sanctuary cities,
which seek
to protect many of those who are
undocumented.

04:30.036 --> 04:34.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president tweeted that the
decision was
-- quote -- "ridiculous" and he
vowed to appeal.

04:34.641 --> 04:40.580 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He lumped that in with criticism
of the 9th
Judicial Circuit, where
appellate courts also

04:40.613 --> 04:42.448 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
blocked his travel ban.

04:42.482 --> 04:44.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Later, he echoed that complaint:

04:44.417 --> 04:48.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States:
I'm never surprised by the 9th
Circuit.

04:48.221 --> 04:49.489 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

04:49.522 --> 04:54.127 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP: As I said, we will
see them
in the Supreme Court.

04:54.160 --> 04:59.065 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Mr. Trump also
told The Washington
Examiner newspaper that he has
considered

04:59.098 --> 05:02.502 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
proposals to split up the 9th
Circuit.

05:02.535 --> 05:07.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, the Department of
Homeland Security
formally opened a new office to
help victims

05:07.707 --> 05:10.910 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of crimes by undocumented
immigrants.

05:10.943 --> 05:15.882 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Secretary John Kelly said that
it will help
shine a light on victims as part
of the president's

05:15.915 --> 05:18.351 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
push on illegal immigration.

05:18.384 --> 05:23.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Multiple studies show that
native-born Americans
are more likely to commit crimes
than are

05:24.023 --> 05:25.792 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
immigrants.

05:25.825 --> 05:30.596 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Trump administration is
going to review
so-called national monument
designations for

05:30.630 --> 05:32.799 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
millions of acres of federal
land.

05:32.832 --> 05:35.601 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They go back to President
Clinton's time in
office.

05:35.635 --> 05:39.105 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Trump ordered the review at
the U.S. Interior
Department today.

05:39.138 --> 05:45.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It is aimed at what he called a
-- quote -- "massive
federal land grab" that bars
drilling, mining

05:45.611 --> 05:47.580 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and other uses.

05:47.613 --> 05:51.951 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Environmental and Native
American tribal groups
denounced the action.

05:51.984 --> 05:53.853 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Wall Street gave a little
ground today.

05:53.886 --> 05:58.591 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
lost 21 points
to close at 20975.

05:58.624 --> 06:05.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq fell a quarter of a
point, and
the S&amp;P 500 slipped one point.

06:05.098 --> 06:09.302 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
I sit down
with White House Budget Director
Mick Mulvaney

06:09.335 --> 06:14.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to talk about the president's
budget and tax
priorities; approaching
President Trump's

06:14.140 --> 06:24.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
first 100 days in office, a look
at what he
has accomplished here at home;
and much more.

06:24.183 --> 06:30.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
first 100 days in office, a look
at what he
has accomplished here at home;
and much more.

06:30.590 --> 06:35.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On this day when the White House
is unveiling
the outline of a tax system
overhaul, and

06:35.762 --> 06:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
negotiating down to the wire
over a federal
spending plan to fund the
government through

06:40.867 --> 06:46.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
September, I sat down with Mick
Mulvaney,
the head of the Office of
Management and Budget.

06:46.873 --> 06:51.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I spoke with him at his office
this afternoon,
before there were reports of a
deal on health

06:51.978 --> 06:54.480 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
care subsidies.

06:54.514 --> 06:56.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Director Mick Mulvaney, thank
you very much
for talking with us.

06:56.682 --> 06:57.917 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY, White House
Budget Director:
Judy, thank you for having me.

06:57.950 --> 07:00.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I do want to
start by asking
you about taxes.

07:00.653 --> 07:03.122 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's the big announcement
coming from the
administration today.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.091 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICK MULVANEY: Sure.

07:05.124 --> 07:09.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The proposal,
among other things,
calls for increases in the
standard deductions,

07:09.328 --> 07:10.296 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
individuals and families.

07:10.329 --> 07:11.464 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MICK MULVANEY: Yes.

07:11.497 --> 07:15.435 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Big cuts in
corporate business
taxes.

07:15.468 --> 07:17.904 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What is the administration
trying to accomplish
with this proposal?

07:17.937 --> 07:22.241 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Getting economic
growth back
where it's supposed to be.

07:22.275 --> 07:26.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think what we have forgotten
for the last
decade is that America used to
be a fast-growing

07:26.679 --> 07:28.481 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
economy.

07:28.514 --> 07:31.751 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If you look over the course of
our 200-plus
years, we're supposed to grow at
about 3 percent,

07:31.784 --> 07:35.555 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
on average, and that's where we
have been
since World War II, at the very
least, even

07:35.588 --> 07:37.023 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
further back than that.

07:37.056 --> 07:39.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, for the last decade, we
have been growing
at less than 2 percent.

07:39.325 --> 07:44.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That doesn't sound like much,
but if you think
about it in terms of the power
of compound

07:44.564 --> 07:49.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
interest, when you take an
economy our size
that only grows 2 percent a year
for a decade,

07:49.569 --> 07:53.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
instead of 3 percent a year, the
difference
between those things are
tremendous.

07:53.506 --> 07:59.412 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Folks who are 30 years old have
never had
a job during a time when the
economy was growing

07:59.445 --> 08:00.413 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
at 3 percent.

08:00.446 --> 08:01.948 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it's entirely different.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.716 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I was a young person, if
you got fired,
you could find another job.

08:03.749 --> 08:06.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you wanted to quit, you could
go start
your own company.

08:06.052 --> 08:07.854 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We haven't had that for 10 years
now.

08:07.887 --> 08:09.689 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we're trying to get back to
that.

08:09.722 --> 08:13.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that is what is driving not
only everything
we do at the White House, but
specifically

08:13.826 --> 08:15.495 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this tax plan.

08:15.528 --> 08:18.431 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: A number of the
analysts who
have looked at say, when you put
together

08:18.464 --> 08:23.503 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the proposed business tax cuts,
some of the
individual cuts, and when you
look at the

08:23.536 --> 08:29.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
proposal to do away with some of
the taxes
that are now in the Affordable
Care Act, in

08:29.475 --> 08:35.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
essence, it's the top 1 percent
of Americans,
1 percent of American,
high-income level,

08:35.815 --> 08:37.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
who are going to benefit the
most from this.

08:37.950 --> 08:39.418 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How do you answer that?

08:39.452 --> 08:42.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: I'm not sure how
could they
could come to that conclusion.

08:42.288 --> 08:46.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would be curious to know what
assumptions
they're making regarding the
value of deductions.

08:46.425 --> 08:51.197 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For example, we get rid of all
the deductions
on the personal side, except, I
think, let's

08:51.230 --> 08:54.734 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
see, charity and some of the
home interest
deduction.

08:54.767 --> 08:59.672 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I'm not sure how you could
make that conclusion,
unless you're making some wild
assumptions

08:59.705 --> 09:01.674 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about the nature of those
deductions.

09:01.707 --> 09:03.943 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Where do you see
the benefits
falling, what income?

09:03.976 --> 09:05.578 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Middle class.

09:05.611 --> 09:09.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Middle class and business, writ
large, both
large business and small
business.

09:09.849 --> 09:15.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In fact, it should be one of the
largest reductions
on small business, what we call
S Corporations,

09:15.855 --> 09:17.723 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in the history of S
Corporations.

09:17.757 --> 09:24.764 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, we're trying to drive the
economic benefit
here to the taxpayers in the
middle, the folks

09:24.797 --> 09:28.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who are in the middle class, who
are paying
the taxes, and the places where
they work.

09:28.034 --> 09:33.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We know the tax
cuts for these
so-called pass-through
businesses, owner-owned

09:33.539 --> 09:36.309 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
businesses, are going to be
among the beneficiaries.

09:36.342 --> 09:40.146 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know President Trump, it's
the kind of
business he has.

09:40.179 --> 09:41.981 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
How much does he stand to
benefit?

09:42.014 --> 09:47.253 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I ask people of because
people are saying,
we don't know what his tax
income situation

09:47.286 --> 09:48.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
is.

09:48.287 --> 09:50.656 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He has said he's not going to
release that.

09:50.690 --> 09:53.793 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How does the public know that he
doesn't stand
to benefit significantly?

09:53.826 --> 09:57.330 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICK MULVANEY: Well, I actually
don't care
about whether or not someone
else benefits.

09:57.363 --> 10:00.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I care about whether I benefit,
I being just
anybody.

10:00.700 --> 10:02.101 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

10:02.134 --> 10:04.503 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
As long as I'm better off, why
should I care
if somebody is as well?

10:04.537 --> 10:07.106 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What I look at through is the
lens of the
business I used to run.

10:07.139 --> 10:08.207 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I owned a restaurant.

