days is John
F. Kennedy, after the Bay of
Pigs.

30:18.983 --> 30:23.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the way he handled that
issue by going
before the American people and
saying, I'm

30:23.822 --> 30:28.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
responsible for this, I'm the
responsible
officer of the government,
caused his approval

30:28.092 --> 30:30.028 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
ratings to spike even further.

30:30.061 --> 30:32.697 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So he comes in with an 83
percent rating.

30:32.730 --> 30:36.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We know Trump's approval ratings
is down in
the low 40s at this point.

30:36.201 --> 30:40.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Dig a little
deeper there,
Michael, in terms of how Donald
Trump has

30:40.238 --> 30:43.007 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
done compared to other
presidents.

30:43.041 --> 30:46.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You started to talk about this a
moment ago
with the setting of the
standard.

30:46.945 --> 30:48.680 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But how does he stack up?

30:48.713 --> 30:51.516 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL BESCHLOSS: Well, you
know, a lot of
this, you know, what presidents
do, above

30:51.549 --> 30:56.387 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
