33:34.479 --> 33:40.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To what extent can we look at
Donald Trump's
first few months in office and
say this forecasts

33:40.118 --> 33:41.886 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
whether he's going to be
successful or not?

33:41.919 --> 33:45.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARBARA PERRY: Well, I'm from
Louisville,
Kentucky, originally, and we're
about to do

33:45.089 --> 33:49.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the Kentucky Derby, so I say a
horse can stumble
out of the gate or it can be
running last

33:49.861 --> 33:50.828 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the first third...

33:50.862 --> 33:51.829 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MICHAEL BESCHLOSS: Absolutely.

33:51.863 --> 33:53.631 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BARBARA PERRY: ... and still
come on to win.

33:53.664 --> 33:58.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, to the point about low
approval ratings
and Michael's point about not
necessarily

33:58.503 --> 34:02.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
accomplishing all of the list of
things he
said he would do in the 100 days
doesn't mean

34:02.440 --> 34:05.476 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he won't be reelected or
that he will
have a failed presidency.

34:05.510 --> 34:10.648 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if you think of someone like
Bill Clinton,
who had a rather chaotic start
in a host of

34:10.681 --> 34:16.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ways in those first 100 days,
and even up
to the Oklahoma City bombing in
1995, and

34:16.554 --> 34:19.624 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
